The paper deals with multiwinner voting systems, which are a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper models these systems as a resource allocation problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing voter satisfaction, which is a topic in social choice theory (cs.SI).
